```sql
GET /my_index/_search
{
  "query": {
    "regexp": {
      "field_name": "string_pattern"
    }
  }
}
```

In this example, replace `/my_index/` with the name of the index you want to search, and `"my_field"` with the name of the field where you want to apply the pattern. Replace `"string_pattern"` with the string pattern you're looking for.
The `string_pattern` can be any valid regular expression, including wildcards like `*`, `\d`, etc.
For example, if you wanted to find all documents containing the word "dog" anywhere in the text, you could use the following query:
```json
GET /my_index/_search
{
  "query": {
    "regexp": {
      "field_name": ".*dog.*"
    }
  }
}
```

